Our%20daughter%20was%20doing%20high%20school%20online%20in%20the%20US%20because%20of%20Covid%2C%20but%20the%20workload%20was%20way%20too%20much.%20She%20was%20taking%20three%20AP%20classes%20and%20doing%20school%20and%20homework%20from%206%20a.m.%20until%20midnight%20every%20day%2C%20including%20weekends.%20There%20was%20no%20work%2Flife%20balance%20at%20that%20time.%20Our%20kids%20are%20now%20able%20to%20spend%20time%20with%20family%20and%20friends%20outside%20school%20and%20enjoy%20their%20time%20here%20because%20there's%20less%20of%20that%20pressure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThere%20are%20things%20we%20miss%20about%20school%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20I%20think%20the%20US%20does%20better%20is%20it%20provides%20more%20school-related%20extracurricular%20activities.%20We%20miss%20that%20aspect%20of%20school%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20kids%20were%20heavily%20involved%20in%20the%20musical%20theater%20program%20in%20their%20schools%20in%20Austin%20and%20they%20played%20instruments%20and%20participated%20in%20school%20sports.%20The%20schools%20that%20our%20kids%20are%20currently%20at%20in%20Portugal%20don't%20have%20many%20extracurricular%20activities.%20Portuguese%20schools%20focus%20on%20teaching%20the%20necessary%20subjects%20for%20future%20education%20and%20employment.%20Typically%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Belective%26quot%3B%20classes%20are%20just%20languages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20noticeable%20concern%20has%20been%20that%20the%20teachers%20go%20on%20strike%20frequently%2C%20which%20can%20cause%20some%20issues%20due%20to%20the%20last-minute%20nature%20of%20the%20cancellations.%20We%20usually%20find%20out%20on%20the%20day%20when%20we're%20turned%20away%20at%20the%20school%20gate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20we%20don't%20usually%20find%20out%20when%20the%20first%20day%20of%20school%20is%20until%20a%20day%20or%20two%20before%20school%20actually%20starts.%20This%20has%20been%20challenging%20for%20us%20as%20we%20like%20to%20know%20ahead%20of%2