2%3Eways%20to%20enjoy%20pizza%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20frozen%20pies%20fresh%20from%20the%20oven%20are%20a%20satisfying%20and%20often%20cost-effective%20way%20to%20eat%20a%20slice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20it%20doesn't%20feel%20worth%20it%20to%20heat%20my%20whole%20oven%20%E2%80%94%20or%20unpack%20all%20the%20baking%20pans%20I%20store%20there.%20So%20that's%20when%20I%20turn%20to%20my%20air%20fryer%20or%20toaster%20oven.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tested%20out%20both%20countertop%20appliances%20to%20see%20which%20one%20makes%20a%20more%20satisfying%20slice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20first%20step%20is%20picking%20out%20the%20right%20kind%20of%20pizza.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22half%20of%20a%20frozen%20pepperoni%20pizza%20cut%20into%20three%20triangles%20on%20a%20wooden%20cutting%20board%20with%20a%20knife%20resting%20to%20the%20side%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a7ead76979d7371823e8ff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20standard%2C%20thin-crust%20frozen%20pizza%20works%20best%20for%20the%20smaller%20appliances.%20%3Cp%3EPriscilla%20Thomas%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20I%20picked%20up%20some%20frozen%20pizzas%20with%20rising%20crusts.%20But%20no%20amount%20of%20time%20could%20bake%20the%20crust%20before%20the%20toppings%20burned%20in%20either%20appliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20recommend%20avoiding%20any%20medium%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpizza-styles-in-the-us-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethick-crust%20pizzas%3C%2Fa%3E%20so%20you%20don't%20end%20up%20with%20uncooked%20dough%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I%20tracked%20down%20the%20perfect%20thin-crust%20pie%2C%20I%20sliced%20the%20pizza%20while%20frozen%20with%20a%20sharp%2C%20strong%20knife.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20lot%20easier%20than%20I%20expected%20to%20cut%20the%20slices.%20Plus%2C%20with%20this%20bit%20of%20prep%2C%20I%20can%20make%20a%20slice%20or%20two%20whenever%20the%20mood%20strikes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EI%20started%20this%20experiment%20with%20my%20air%20fryer.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22slice%20of%20pepperoni%20pizza%20in%20an%20air%20fryer%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a7ec84dcdb354a98582f5c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20toppings%20got%20a%20little%20disheveled%20in%20my%20air%20fryer.%20%3Cp%3EPriscilla%20Thomas%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20preheated%20my%20air%20fryer%20to%20400%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%20for%2015%20minutes%20before%20cooking%20one%20slice%20of%20frozen%20pizza%20for%20six%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20point%2C%20the%20cheese%20was%20melted%20and%20crisping%20at%20the%20edges%2C%20but%20most%20of%20the%20pepperoni%20blew%20off%20(probably%20because%20of%20the%20circulating%20air).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20few%20pieces%20of%20pepperoni%20left%20were%20mostly%20burnt%2C%20and%20the%20crust%20was%20still%20pale%20and%20underbaked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20put%20this%20slice%20back%20in%20for%20another%20two%20minutes%20to%20try%20to%20salvage%20the%20crust%2C%20but%20it%20ended%20up%20being%20cracker-like%20along%20the%20edges%20and%20too%20soft%20in%20the%20middle.%20Plus%2C%20the%20toppings%20were%20dry%20and%20overcooked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EI%20decided%20to%20try%20again%20with%20the%20air%20fryer%20%E2%80%94%20this%20time%20accounting%20for%20my%20past%20mistakes.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22underside%20of%20a%20slice%20of%20frozen%20pizza%20with%20divets%20poked%20into%20the%20crust%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a7ee216979d7371823ec5c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EI%20poked%20some%20holes%20in%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20crust%20to%20try%20to%20get%20it%20to%20cook%20better.%20%3Cp%3EPriscilla%20Thomas%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20prepped%20the%20slice%20for%20my%20second%20attempt%20by%20poking%20the%20underside%20of%20the%20crust%20with%20a%20fork%20to%20make%20shallow%20holes.%20I%20also%20spritzed%20it%20with%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fkitchen%2Fbest-olive-oil%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eolive%20oil%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20preheating%20the%20air%20fryer%20at%20400%20F%2C%20I%20lowered%20the%20temperature%20to%20375%20F%20and%20cooked%20the%20slice%20for%20seven%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EI%20couldn't%20seem%20to%20get%20the%20temperature%20and%20timing%20right%20in%20my%20air%20fryer.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222663%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22slice%20of%20burnt%20pepperoni%20pizza%20in%20an%20air%20fryer%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a7ed00dcdb354a98582fb7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221997%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20pizza%20ended%20up%20being%20too%20crispy%20along%20the%20outside%20and%20underdone%20in%20the%20center.%3Cp%3EPriscilla%20Thomas%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20toppings%20cooked%20well%2C%20and%20I%20even%20got%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DQeZcNxC6r2U%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epieces%20of%20pepperoni%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20were%20crispy%20at%20the%20edges%20without%20turning%20to%20dust%20in%20my%20mouth.%20But%20the%20underside%20of%20the%20crust%20never%20got%20toasty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tried%20yet%20another%20slice%20with%20this%20prep%20and%20temperature%20but%20cooked%20it%20for%2010%20minutes.%20Sadly%2C%20it%20was%20too%20long%20for%20the%20pepperoni%2C%20and%20it%20made%20the%20outer%20edge%20of%20the%20crust%20dry%20and%20brittle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EI%20moved%20on%20to%20my%20toaster%20oven%2C%20hoping%20for%20better%20results.%3Cfig