%20the%20background%20lights%20slowly%20dimmed%20throughout%20the%20course%20of%20the%20TikTok%2C%20he%20insisted%20the%20correct%20past%20tense%20was%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20%26quot%3Bgaslated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20falsely%20claimed%20that%20the%20root%20of%20the%20word%20%26quot%3Blight%26quot%3B%20also%20led%20to%20the%20past%20tenses%20%26quot%3Billuminated%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Belucidated%2C%26quot%3B%20suggesting%20-ated%20is%20the%20correct%20suffix%20for%20all%20light-related%20words.%20(In%20fact%2C%20%26quot%3Billuminate%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Belucidate%26quot%3B%20come%20from%20Latin%2C%20while%20%26quot%3Blight%26quot%3B%20has%20Germanic%20origins%2C%20and%20of%20course%20the%20past%20tense%20of%20%26quot%3Bto%20light%26quot%3B%20is%20undoubtedly%20%26quot%3Blit.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAleksic%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20thought%20the%20whole%20explanation%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20pretty%20obvious%20bit%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20not%20everyone%20picked%20up%20on%20the%20joke.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20upload%20received%201.3%20million%20views%20and%20over%202%2C200%20comments.%20Many%20joked%20that%20Aleksic%20was%20trying%20to%20gaslight%20them%20into%20using%20the%20wrong%20word%20but%20others%20appeared%20fully%20convinced%20that%20%26quot%3Bgaslated%26quot%3B%20was%20correct.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20guess%20that's%20what%20happens%20when%20you%20build%20up%20credibility%20for%20a%20while%20only%20to%20bait%20and%20switch%20with%20a%20manipulative%20meme%20video%2C%26quot%3B%20Aleksic%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20turns%20out%20none%20of%20the%20options%20are%20exactly%20wrong%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Laura%20Bailey%2C%20a%20senior%20lecturer%20in%20English%20language%20and%20linguistics%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Kent%2C%20England%2C%20confirmed%20to%20BI%20that%20Aleksic's%20video%20was%20recognizably%20a%20joke%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20couldn't%20quite%20settle%20the%20issue%20of%20what%20the%20right%20answer%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20English%20language%20doesn't%20have%20an%20official%20body%20that%20governs%20its%20%26quot%3Bcorrect%26quot%3B%20use%2C%20although%20dictionaries%20are%20often%20used%20as%20the%20arbiter%20of%20what%20is%20right%20and%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linguisticsociety.org%2Fresource%2Fwhat-correct-language%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELinguistic%20Society%20of%20America%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BEnglish%20is%20now%20changing%20in%20exactly%20the%20same%20ways%20that%20have%20contributed%20to%20making%20it%20the%20rich%2C%20flexible%2C%20and%20adaptable%20language%20so%20popular%20throughout%20the%20world%20today.%20Living%20languages%20must%20change%2C%20must%20adapt%2C%20must%20grow.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBailey%20agreed%20with%20Merriam-Webster%20that%20the%20word%20you're%20looking%20for%20is%20probably%20%26quot%3Bgaslighted%2C%26quot%3B%20treating%20it%20as%20a%20regular%20verb%20that%20would%20take%20the%20suffix%20-ed%20for%20the%20past%20tense.%20But%20she%20said%20%26quot%3Bgaslit%26quot%3B%20also%20works%20for%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLinguists%20don't%20tell%20people%20what's%20correct%2C%20only%20what%20people%20actually%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAleksic%20echoed%20this%20sentiment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDon't%20ever%20trust%20a%20linguist%20who%20tells%20you%20how%20language%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20used%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20only%20here%20to%20observe%2C%20not%20to%20tell%20you%20what%20to%20say.%20But%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20I%20can't%20goof%20around%20with%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20if%20Aleksic's%20%26quot%3Bgaslated%26quot%3B%20is%20your%20preferred%20option%2C%20no%20need%20to%20let%20the%20fact%20that%20it's%20made%20up%20put%20you%20off%20using%20it%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20you%20do%20get%20some%20confused%20looks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgaslit-gaslighting-past-tense-liguistics-expert-internet-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705840441000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a9534ddcdb354a98589b19%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgaslit-gaslighting-past-tense-liguistics-expert-internet-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Is%20the%20past%20tense%20of%20%26quot%3Bgaslight%26quot%3B%20gaslighted%20or%20gaslit%3F%20After%20a%20third%20option%20went%20viral%2C%20we%20asked%20linguists%20to%20settle%20the%20debate.%20But%20it%20turns%20out%20it's%20complicated.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22andrewlloyd%40insider.com%20(Andrew%20Lloyd)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgaslit-gaslighting-past-tense-liguistics-expert-internet-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Average%20selling%20price%20of%20passenger%20vehicles%20in%20India%20up%20by%2050%25%20in%205%20years%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705840306000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2018-12%2F11%2Ffull%2F1544473019-7978.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findustry%2Fauto%2Faverage-selling-price-of-passenger-vehicles-rises-by-50-in-last-5-years-124012100104_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22ASP%20has%20gone%20up%20from%20Rs%207.65%20lakh%20in%202018-19%20to%20Rs%2011.5%20lakh%20in%202023-24%2C%20according%20to%20the%20industry.%20Premiumisation%2C%20changing%20regulatory%20norms%20and%20SUV%20craze%20lead%20to%20price%20hikes%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findustry%2Fauto%2Faverage-selling-price-of-passenger-vehicles-rises-by-50-in-last-5-years-124012100104_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%