roved%20life-changing.%20%26quot%3BWhy%20don't%20you%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-discovered-the-power-of-handwritten-letters-over-social-media-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrite%20to%20him%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20asked.%20And%20that's%20how%20our%20friendship%20began.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDespite%20being%20separated%20by%20oceans%20and%20years%2C%20my%20great-uncle%20became%20a%20dear%20friend%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20great-uncle%20was%20born%20in%201921%2C%20meaning%20we%20had%20an%20age%20gap%20of%20over%2070%20years.%20He%20lived%20in%20Cornwall%2C%20England%3B%20I%20lived%20near%20Canberra%2C%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20hindsight%2C%20I%20was%20naive%20in%20entering%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpen-pals-late-mother-best-friend-intergenerational-friendship-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecorrespondence%20with%20him%3C%2Fa%3E.%20To%20what%20extent%20could%20a%20teenager%2C%20with%20all%20her%20adolescent%20preoccupations%20and%20limited%20life%20experience%2C%20really%20prove%20an%20engaging%20letter-writer%20for%20someone%20in%20their%20late%2080s%3F%20Would%20my%20youth%20be%20uplifting%20or%20depressing%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20to%20a%20widower%20who%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F9-famous-people-who-served-during-world-war%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efought%20in%20a%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20raised%20two%20children%2C%20and%20outlived%20them%20both%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20ask%20these%20questions%20%E2%80%94%20and%20my%20mother%2C%20aware%20of%20how%20lonely%20my%20great-uncle%20was%2C%20intuited%20that%20my%20letters%2C%20for%20all%20their%20youth%20and%20ingenuousness%2C%20would%20likely%20at%20least%20be%20entertaining%20(consciously%20or%20otherwise)%20and%20would%20offer%20him%20something%20to%20look%20forward%20to.%20In%20fairness%2C%20people%20of%20all%20ages%20and%20stripes%20can%20be%20interesting%20if%20one%20approaches%20them%20with%20curiosity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20so%20I%20sent%20my%20first%20letter%2C%20enclosed%20in%20a%20white%20envelope%20with%20stamps%20showing%20bilbies%2C%20quokkas%2C%20and%20emus.%20My%20great-uncle%20wrote%20back%20swiftly%20and%20at%20length.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOur%20friendship%20changed%20the%20direction%20of%20my%20adult%20life%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20our%20surprise%2C%20we%20had%20plenty%20in%20common.%20Like%20me%2C%20my%20great-uncle%20adored%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmap-shows-hardest-languages-to-learn-2017-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elanguages%20and%20words%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20potentially%20more%20so%20than%20any%20of%20my%20other%20family%20members%20%E2%80%94%20and%20gave%20me%20the%20encouragement%20I%20needed%20to%20pursue%20a%20study%20path%20in%20literature%20and%20languages%20that%20I%20found%20rich%20and%20fulfilling%2C%C2%A0even%20though%20he%20himself%20had%20received%20limited%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20also%20wickedly%20funny%20and%20simultaneously%C2%A0deeply%20sad%20following%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-how-long-soon-date-after-death-of-spouse-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeath%20of%20his%20wife%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20second%20daughter%2C%20and%20his%20openness%20about%20his%20experiences%20was%20generous%20and%20formative%20in%20terms%20of%20me%20better%20understanding%20the%20emotional%20complexities%20of%20people%20much%20older%20than%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20what%20was%20perhaps%20overall%20so%20significant%20about%20this%20friendship%2C%20for%20me%2C%20was%20that%20here%20was%20a%20fully%20cognisant%2C%20older%20man%2C%20self-aware%20and%20open%20to%20communicating%20%E2%80%94%20but%20only%20via%20letters%2C%20and%20only%2C%20I%20realize%20now%20in%20hindsight%2C%20with%20someone%20young%20enough%20not%20to%20be%20overwhelmed%20by%20the%20sadnesses%20in%20his%20life%2C%20because%20I%20couldn't%20entirely%20comprehend%20or%20contextualize%20them.%20In%20that%20sense%2C%20we%20both%20offered%20something%20to%20one%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20opened%20up%20to%20me%20about%20topics%20ranging%20from%20surviving%20a%20childhood%C2%A0home%20in%20which%C2%A0his%20father%20was%20physically%20violent%20to%20being%20a%20pilot%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworld-war-ii-historian-rates-wwii-movies-tv-realism-2022%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorld%20War%20II%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20wrote%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoctors-explain-why-people-feel-better-near-the-ocean-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewalking%20along%20a%20beach%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20an%20airstrike%2C%20certain%20he%20would%20be%20killed%20the%20following%20day.%20He%20told%20me%20how%20much%20my%20great-aunt%20had%20improved%20his%20life%2C%20even%20though%20he%20sometimes%20feared%20he%20hadn't%20been%20all%20she%20might%20have%20hoped%20for%20from%20a%20husband.%20He%20went%20sailing%20with%20her%20for%20years%20despite%20being%20less%20keen%20on%20open%20waters%20than%20she%20was.%20They%20sailed%20well%20into%20their%2070s%20all%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHis%20friendship%20has%20been%20a%20lasting%20gift%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20several%20years%20of%20writing%20to%20my%20great-uncle%2C%20I%20met%20up%20with%20him%20in%20England%20following%20a%20stint%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdecision-swap-nanny-for-au-pair-best-ever-made-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworking%20as%20an%20au%20pair%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Italy.%20I%20traveled%C2%A0by%20bus%20and%20train%20to%C2%A0where%20he%20lived%20in%C2%A0Cornwall%2C%20crocheting%20a%20blanket%20for%20him%20en%C2%A0route%3B%20he%20later%20took%20this%20blanket%20with%20him%20to%20his%20retirement%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20stayed%20with%20him%20for%20several%20days.%20With%20his%20limited%20appetite%2C%20he%20took%20great%20pleasure%20in%20seeing%20how%20many%20biscuits%20I%20could%20eat%20and%20continuously%20offered%20me%20food.%20He%20showed%20me%20his%20study%20and%20his%20books%3B%20he%20was%20in%20his%2090s%20at%20this%20point%2C%20yet%20was%20busy%20studying%20Norwegian%20for%20fun%20and%20revisiting%20Tolstoy%20in%20the%20original.%20During%20the%20war%2C%20he%20had%20learned%20the%20native%20languages%20of%20various%20airmen%20from%20occupied%20eastern%20Europe%20who%20were%20serving%20alongside%20the%20British%3B%20he%20then%20continued%20teaching%20himself%20languages%20throughout%20his%20lifetime.%20As%20someone%20who%20also%20loves%20languages%2C%20writing%2C%20and%20talking%20to%20many%20different%20people%2C%20his%20undimmed%20intellectual%20curiosity%20proved%20inspiring%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20recently%20revisited%20Cornwall%2C%20now%20in%20my%20late%2020s%3B%20the%20train%20passed%20by%20the%20station%20where%20I%20saw%20him%20last%2C%20standing%20just%20behind%20the%20barriers.%20I%20had%20known%20when%20farewelling%20him%20that%20I%20would%20never%20see%20him%20again.%20Passing%20that%20station%20once%20more%20and%20the%20space%20where%20he%20had%20stood%20felt%20especially%20poignant.%20I%20potentially%20wouldn't%20be%20in%20the%20UK%20%E2%80%94%20wouldn't%20have%20made%20it%20to%20Cambridge%20to%20study%20literature%20and%20languages%20%E2%80%94%20if%20it%20hadn't%20been%20for%20him.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20additional%20ongoing%20gift%20from%20my%20friendship%20with%20my%20great-uncle%20is%20that%20of%20writing%20letters.%20Since%20writing%20to%20him%20and%20realizing%20how%20differently%20%E2%80%94%20and%20beautifully%20%E2%80%94%20people%20sometimes%20express%20themselves%20in%20long-form%20handwriting%2C%20I%20began%20writing%20letters%20to%20friends%20and%20receiving%20letters%20in%20turn.%20Over%20the%20past%20decade%20or