ks%20from%201928%2C%20stating%20that%20in%20India%20%E2%80%9Cpolitics%20is%20nothing%20but%20theology%20in%20action%2C%20should%20remind%20us%20that%20this%20goes%20against%20the%20constitution%20and%20constitutional%20morality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmbedkar%E2%80%99s%20words%20resonate%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20consecration%20ceremony%20and%20the%20ritual%20ridden%20politics%20flowing%20from%20it.%20Ambedkar%20made%20that%20statement%20in%20his%20submission%20before%20the%20Indian%20Statutory%20Commission%20on%20May%2029%2C%201928%20concerning%20the%20safeguards%20for%20the%20protection%20of%20the%20interests%20of%20Depressed%20Classes%20as%20a%20minority%20on%20behalf%20of%20Bahishkrita%20Hitakarini%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20illuminating%20to%20note%20that%20he%2C%20while%20making%20those%20remarks%20with%20anguish%2C%20put%20forth%20profound%20observations%20on%20secularism.%20He%20said%20%E2%80%9CIf%20representative%20government%20is%20so%20weak%20when%20operating%20among%20European%20peoples%2C%20where%20the%20secularisation%20of%20politics%20has%20gone%20far%20further%2C%20how%20much%20weaker%20must%20it%20be%20in%20India%20where%20politics%20is%20nothing%20but%20theology%20in%20action.%E2%80%9D%20He%20linked%20the%20quality%20of%20strength%20of%20representative%20government%20with%20the%20secularisation%20of%20politics%20in%20Europe%20and%20expressed%20his%20hopelessness%20regarding%20the%20future%20of%20representative%20government%20in%20India%20where%20politics%20was%20not%20rooted%20in%20secular%20values.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Findian-civilisation-is-being-disrobed-in-the-city-of-ram%5C%22%3EIndian%20Civilisation%20Is%20Being%20Disrobed%20in%20the%20City%20of%20Ram%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20articulations%20are%20making%20the%20citizenry%20sensitive%20to%20the%20present%20day%20developments%20engineered%20by%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20leaders%20controlling%20the%20state%20apparatus%20and%20pursuing%20politics%20bereft%20of%20secular%20attributes%20with%20open%20and%20aggressive%20push%20in%20favour%20of%20majoritarianism%20and%20polarisation%20process.%20Ambedkar%20also%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20this%20theology%20against%20which%20the%20Depressed%20classes%20must%20seek%20to%20be%20protected.%E2%80%9D%20Indeed%20such%20politics%20anchored%20in%20theology%20is%20bound%20to%20weaken%20the%20government%20and%20the%20unmistakable%20signs%20in%20this%20regard%20are%20visible%20in%20a%20sinister%20form.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20wonder%20that%20India%20is%20seen%20as%20country%20of%20particular%20concern%20on%20the%20status%20of%20religious%20freedom.%20It%20has%20also%20been%20described%20as%20an%20elected%20autocracy.%20Such%20concerns%20can%20be%20explained%20in%20terms%20of%20spread%20of%20sectarianism%20and%20bigotry%20and%20the%20forces%20emerging%20out%20of%20such%20developments%20are%20now%20openly%20espousing%20the%20cause%20of%20fanaticism.%20Such%20sinister%20phenomenon%20is%20bound%20to%20get%20multiplied%20with%20theology%20remaining%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20politics%20and%20demonstrated%20vigorously%20all%20over%20the%20country%20on%20the%20occasion%20of%20the%20consecration%20of%20the%20Ram%20temple%20in%20Ayodhya.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGandhi%E2%80%99s%20stand%20against%20theocratic%20state%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20India%20was%20never%20conceived%20on%20theological%20grounds%20was%20affirmed%20by%20none%20other%20than%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20on%20November%2028%2C%201947%20during%20a%20prayer%20meeting%20in%20Delhi.%20He%20did%20so%20when%20some%20leaders%20entertained%20the%20idea%2C%20during%20the%20early%20phase%20of%20our%20independence%2C%20for%20mobilising%20money%20from%20government%20treasury%20for%20reconstruction%20of%20the%20Somnath%20temple%20in%20Gujarat.%20Noting%20that%20the%20government%20formed%20after%20independence%20was%20for%20all%20Indians%20regardless%20of%20their%20faiths%2C%20Gandhi%20asserted%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20secular%20government%2C%20that%20is%2C%20it%20is%20not%20a%20theocratic%20government%2C%20rather%2C%20it%20does%20not%20belong%20to%20any%20particular%20religion.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20that%20reasoning%20he%20asked%20Sardar%20Vallabhbhai%20Patel%20if%20government%20funds%20were%20being%20used%20for%20restoration%20of%20the%20temple.%20Patel%20informed%20Gandhi%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%20would%20be%20gross%20%3Cem%3Eadharma%3C%2Fem%3E%20if%20either%20the%20Junagadh%20government%20or%20the%20Union%20government%20gives%20money%20for%20the%20renovation%20of%20the%20Somnath%20temple%E2%80%9D.%20Patel%20then%20forcefully%20took%20a%20stand%20that%20%E2%80%9Cso%20long%20as%20he%20was%20alive%E2%80%A6.%20not%20a%20single%20pie%20could%20be%20taken%20out%20from%20the%20treasury%20of%20Junagadh%20for%20the%20renovation%20of%20the%20Somnath%20temple.%E2%80%9D%20Eventually%20Patel%20mobilised%20money%20from%20the%20public%20for%20restoration%20of%20Somnath%20temple%20and%20it%20was%20a%20clear%20vindication%20of%20the%20secular%20nature%20of%20the%20Indian%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgender%2Fwhat-happens-in-ayodhya-doesnt-stay-in-ayodhya%5C%22%3EWhat%20Happens%20in%20Ayodhya%20Doesn%E2%80%99t%20Stay%20in%20Ayodhya%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESecular%20state%20and%20representative%20government%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBecause%20such%20secular%20nature%20was%20upheld%20by%20the%20leadership%20of%20that%20time%2C%20politics%20that%20accompanied%20it%20remained%20largely%20secular%20and%20eschewed%20theology.%20Sadly%2C%20secularism%20today%20is%20badly%20compromised%20and%20theology%20has%20taken%20centre%20stage.%20The%20active%20involvement%20of%20the%20state%20and%20of%20the%20ruling%20leaders%20occupying%20constitutional%20positions%20constitute%20an%20unmistakable%20assault%20on%20the%20secularism%20held%20to%20be%20the%20basic%20structure%20of%20the%20constitution%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Somnath%20temple%20was%20consecrated%2C%20then%20President%20of%20India%2C%20Rajendra%20Prasad%2C%20accepted%20the%20invitation%20and%20sought%20Prime%20Minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20views.%20Nehru%20suggested%20that%20there%20was%20no%20problem%20if%20the%20president%20visited%20the%20shrines%20but%20persuasively%20argued%20against%20him%20participating%20in%20any%20special%20event%20connected%20with%20their%20consecrations.%20He%20argued%20that%20participation%20in%20those%20special%20events%20had%20other%20implications%20and%20thus%20requested%20him%20to%20avoid%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENehru%20was%20not%20alone%20in%20taking%20such%20a%20stand.%20Even%20C.%20Rajagopalachari%20and%20S.%20Radhakrishnan%20requested%20President%20Prasad%20to%20stay%20away%20from%20that%20event.%20All%20these%20points%20are%20there%20in%20several%20writings%20of%20Nehru.%20But%20Prasad%20participated%20in%20his%20individual%20capacity.%20There%20were%20leaders%20like%20Nehru%2C%20Rajagopalachari%20and%20Radhakrishnan%20who%20took%20a%20stand%20in%20tune%20with%20the%20constitutional%20vision%20of%20India%20devoid%20of%20any%20theology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20contrary%20can%20be%20observed%20in%20the%20case%20of%20the%20Ram%20temple.%20The%20present%20day%20government%E2%80%99s%20stand%20is%20rooted%20in%20theology%20and%20the%20politics%20shaped%20by%20it%20is%20putting%20India%E2%80%99s%20secular%20credentials%20at%20stake.%20It%20has%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20put%20in%20reverse%20gear%20the%20secularisation%20of%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20dangerous%20process%20need%20to%20be%20stemmed%20to%20salvage%20politics%20from%20the%20clutches%20of%20those%20giving%20primacy%20to%20theology.%20There%20is%20an%20urgent%20necessity%20yet%20again%20to%20fast%20track%20politics%20on%20secular%20values.%20That%20would%20constitute%20a%20real%20tribute%20to%20Gandhi%2C%20Nehru%20and%20Ambedkar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ES.%20N.%20Sahu%20served%20as%20Officer%20on%20Special%20Duty%20to%20President%20of%20India%20K%20R%20Narayanan%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705833910000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F12193806%2Fimage-1732.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftheologically-determined-politics-weakens-representative-government%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20active%20involvement%20of%20the%20state%20and%20of%20the%20ruling%20leaders%20occupying%20constitutional%20positions%20is%20an%20unmistakable%20assault%20on%20India's%20secular%20values.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftheologically-determined-politics-weakens-representative-government%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bwari%20kidnapping%3A%20Nigeria%20police%20secure%20release%20of%20sisters%20taken%20from%20Abuja%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705833706000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F7662%2Fproduction%2F_132360303_sisters976.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-68047140%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20girls%20were%20kidnapped%20from%20their%20home%20in%20Abuja%2C%20along%20with%20another%20sister%20who%20was%20later%20killed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A254%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-68047140%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-68047140.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-68047140.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rohit%20Shetty%20reveals%20why%20his%20father%20was%20h