0Theatre%2C%20which%20had%20just%20staged%20the%20first%20professional%20US%20performance%20of%C2%A0%3Cem%3ENagamandala%3C%2Fem%3E.%20He%20wrote%20it%20in%20Kannada%2C%20and%20translated%20it%20into%20English%20right%20afterward.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20split%20between%20nature%20and%20culture%2C%20body%20and%20mind%20appears%20in%20such%20earlier%20plays%20as%C2%A0%3Cem%3EHayavadana%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Cem%3EBali%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20but%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3EAgni%20Mattu%20Male%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0the%20duality%20is%20expressed%20for%20the%20first%20time%20as%20the%20explicit%20opposition%20between%20brahmin%20and%20shudra%2C%E2%80%9D%20Aparna%20Dharwadker%20observes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20Anmol%20Tikoo%20again%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20%3Cem%3EFire%20and%20the%20Rain%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20he%20creates%20this%20intricate%20structure%2C%20including%20a%20play%20within%20the%20play%2C%20that%20allows%20us%20to%20look%20beyond%20the%20elites%20and%20their%20obsessions.%20This%20is%20the%20fire%20versus%20the%20rain%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Agni%20of%20the%20dominant%20castes%20and%20their%20scriptures%2C%20versus%20the%20Male%20of%20ordinary%20folks%2C%20their%20art%20and%20their%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Mahabharata%20is%20about%20the%20difficulty%20of%20being%20good%2C%20then%C2%A0%3Cem%3EFire%20and%20the%20Rain%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0gives%20a%20positive%20counter%20to%20that%20in%20the%20transgressive%20love%20of%20Arvasu%20and%20Nittilai.%20Caring%20for%20others%2C%20those%20who%20aren%E2%80%99t%20akin%20to%20us%2C%20is%20what%20keeps%20the%20world%20going%20and%20that%20is%20what%20turns%20out%20to%20be%20the%20natural%20order%20of%20things.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EListen%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbangaloreinternationalcentre.org%2Faudio%2F182-girishkarnad8-9-the-river-has-no-fear-of-memories-being-an-existentialist%2F%5C%22%3Eepisode%208%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20River%20Has%20No%20Fear%20of%20Memories%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20where%20Karnad%20speaks%20to%20Tikoo%20and%20Arshia%20Sattar%20about%20the%20Mahabharata%2C%20history%2C%20and%20much%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Fire%20and%20the%20Rain%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0evoked%20a%20rare%20%E2%80%9Cintensity%20of%20responses%2C%20both%20negative%20and%20positive%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dharwadker%20writes%2C%20which%20are%20easily%20explained%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20dense%2C%20intellectually%20ambitious%2C%20autumnal%20play%20structured%20around%20ideas%E2%80%A6%20and%20a%20plethora%20of%20tangled%20relationships%20which%20unfold%20with%20a%20rare%20economy%20and%20intensity%20of%20words%20and%20emotions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20472px)%2085vw%2C%20472px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21132854%2Fb15cfc4e-ff82-4cdb-8dfc-5c4ad9e2814d.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22472%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21132854%2Fb15cfc4e-ff82-4cdb-8dfc-5c4ad9e2814d.jpg%201080w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21132854%2Fb15cfc4e-ff82-4cdb-8dfc-5c4ad9e2814d-300x300.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21132854%2Fb15cfc4e-ff82-4cdb-8dfc-5c4ad9e2814d-1024x1024.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21132854%2Fb15cfc4e-ff82-4cdb-8dfc-5c4ad9e2814d-150x150.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-693866%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22472%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAgni%20Jol%2C%20Nayabad%20Titas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20responses%20to%20the%20play%2C%20by%20Shanta%20Gokhale%20and%20Manu%20Chakravarthy%2C%20capture%20this%20breadth%20of%20critical%20responses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShanta%20Gokhale%20hailed%20it%20as%20a%20play%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccannot%20be%20reduced%20to%20an%20indoor%20performance.%20It%20should%20really%20be%20an%20annual%20ritual%2C%20enacted%20under%20the%20open%20sky%20by%20actors%20with%20resonant%20voices%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20327px)%2085vw%2C%20327px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21132953%2F6fd3651f-211a-43ad-acf6-8f68f91cd4e3.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22327%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21132953%2F6fd3651f-211a-43ad-acf6-8f68f91cd4e3.jpg%20540w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21132953%2F6fd3651f-211a-43ad-acf6-8f68f91cd4e3-220x300.jpg%20220w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-693867%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22447%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManu%20Chakravarthy%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20interrogated%20Karnad%20for%20even%20choosing%20the%20vehicle%20of%20Hindu%20myth.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20Karnad%E2%80%99s%20faith%20rests%20entirely%20on%20secular%20elements%2C%20why%20does%20he%20dig%20into%20the%20past%20as%20he%20very%20often%20does%20in%20his%20plays%2C%20drawing%20from%20mythological%20and%20historical%20sources%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21143450%2F9dfcfc8f-c368-4cf3-ba5f-d74182bc2245.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22621%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21143450%2F9dfcfc8f-c368-4cf3-ba5f-d74182bc2245.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21143450%2F9dfcfc8f-c368-4cf3-ba5f-d74182bc2245-300x183.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F21143450%2F9dfcfc8f-c368-4cf3-ba5f-d74182bc2245-1024x624.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-693874%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22378%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%201999%20interview%20with%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Sunday%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Karnad%20explained%20what%20drew%20him%20to%20mythological%20sources%20%E2%80%94%20the%20potential%20for%20exploring%20contemporary%20life%20through%20the%20material%20provided%20by%20Puranic%20legends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPauranic%20plays%20have%20come%20to%20mean%20plays%20about%20Rama%20and%20Krishna%2C%20which%20involve%20bhakti.%20But%20there%20is%20so%20much%20else%20that%20is%20from%20the%20Puranas%2C%20there%20are%20such%20marvellous%20stories%2C%20which%20don%E2%80%99t%20involve%20the%20gods%20at%20all.%20They%20don%E2%80%99t%20involve%20Rama%20or%20Krishna.%20In%20the%20Vedas%20you%20find%20something%2C%20in%20the%20Upanishads%20you%20find%20them.%20%5B%3Cem%3EAgni%20Mattu%20Mal%C3%A9%3C%2Fem%3E%5D%20is%20about%20a%20story%20from%20the%20Mahabharata%2C%20but%20which%20does%20not%20involve%20Rama%2C%20Krishna%20or%20any%20of%20the%20gods.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20Vedic%20tale.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20playwriting%20was%20concerned%2C%20he%20said%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20story%20may%20be%20from%20the%20past.%20But%20the%20play%20must%20be%20about%20the%20present%E2%80%A6%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20deliberately%20try%20to%20make%20it%20a%20contemporary%20subject.%20If%20I%20have%20a%20contemporary%20consciousness%2C%20it%20will%20become%20modern%20because%20I%20am%20a%20modern%20writer%20writing%20about%20it%2C%20you%20see.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20Mahabharata%20was%20not%20just%20a%20store%20of%20minor%20legends%20from%20which%20to%20elicit%20modern%20literature.%20Karnad%20had%20an%20abiding%2C%20overarching%20interest%20in%20the%20central%20story%20of%20the%20Mahabharata%20war%20%E2%80%94%20and%20its%20potency%20in%20Indian%20history%20and%20society%2C%20even%20in%20the%20present%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20f