n%20unanimous%20judgment%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20temple%20side%20on%20November%209%2C%202019%20where%20it%20said%20that%20although%20the%20demolition%20of%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20was%20illegal%2C%20the%20Hindu%20plaintiffs%20laying%20claim%20to%20the%20disputed%202.77%20acres%20of%20land%20made%20a%20better%20case.%20The%20case%2C%20the%20judges%20said%2C%20was%20based%20on%20evidence%20pertaining%20to%20the%20claim%20of%20ownership%20of%20the%20disputed%20land%2C%20not%20faith%20or%20religion.%20The%20judgment%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20was%20also%20the%20first%20not%20to%20have%20the%20name%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncidentally%2C%20Justice%20Bhushan%20was%20the%20only%20one%20among%20the%20five%20to%20have%20made%20a%20separate%20116-page%20concurring%20opinion%20on%20the%20matter%2C%20but%20then%20CJI%20Gogoi%20eventually%20managed%20a%20consensus%20and%20added%20Justice%20Bhushan%E2%80%99s%20opinion%20as%20%E2%80%9Caddenda%E2%80%9D%2C%20a%20first%20in%20the%20history%20of%20the%20apex%20court.%20The%20addenda%20examines%20the%20oral%20and%20documentary%20evidence%20presented%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20about%20Ayodhya%20and%20the%20site%20of%20Babri%20Masjid%20as%20Lord%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20birthplace.%20However%2C%20the%20bench%20decided%20to%20hand%20over%20the%20site%20to%20the%20Hindu%20site%20not%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20those%20questions%20but%20quoted%20evidence%20regarding%20the%20competing%20claims%20of%20the%20disputed%20land%E2%80%99s%20possession.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705828519000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F09194806%2F2019_11img09_Nov_2019_PTI11_9_2019_000298B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fonly-one-of-5-sc-judges-who-passed-ayodhya-verdict-to-attend-ram-temple-ceremony%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Justice%20Bhushan%2C%20who%20is%20currently%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20National%20Compan